There have been a few questions regarding the change to the CMS backpack policy- Students will be allowed full sized backpacks for the 2020-2021 school year. (Previously students were only allowed sling bags.) Students will not be assigned lockers this year and we want to ensure they can comfortably carry their personal items from class to class. Full sized backpacks will be allowed. If you have any questions regarding the Re-Entry Plan please reach out to Mrs. Shoemaker at mshoemaker@ccr2.org.

Happy Monday! Teachers will be sending out emails today for 2020-21 class placement. If you do not receive an email from you child's teacher for this fall by the end of the day, please feel free to email Mr. Cross at jcross@ccr2.org for that information tomorrow.

Also, please remember to sign up for Summer School! Enrollment closes July 1st, and we are excited to have students with us! Protective face coverings such as face masks will be optional, and we will be taking every safety precaution possible to keep our kids socially distanced. We are also currently working on plans to still have the kids out on the playground occasionally to make sure this summer school is an academic but fun time!

Cuba High School Drill Team
May 19 at 5:25 PM 路

Future Drill Team Ladies! Tryouts will be June 2nd-4th at the high school! Practice times will be the 2nd/3rd from 9-2. Tryout day will be the 4th from 11-1. YOU MUST HAVE A PHYSICAL ON FILE WITH US TO PARTICIPATE IN TRYOUTS. This must be a MSHSAA official form which can be found on the school website under "Students" or can be emailed to you to print.

If you are interested in trying out, you MUST send an email to Ms. Cooley to be put on the list and receive more information (acooley@cuba.k12.mo.us). Please do not show up unannounced the day of tryouts. We need to plan for a required amount of space due to Covid restrictions. In the email, please list the name and grade of who is trying out and whether or not a physical is already on file at the high school. Remember- physicals now last for two years. If you are unsure about whether your physical is still good, let us know.

After emailing, you will be sent more information about how everything will work. Can't wait to see everyone and good luck!!

post_text: Attached you will find next weeks learning opportunities for your children. We know this time can be very frustrating and challenging, but we are here to help. If there are assignments that require internet, and you do not have access, then dont do them. We are not going to require work to be turned in for the time being. Any work that students complete and turn in will only help their grade and will not hurt it. It is important that our kids still do the work so they do not get behind, but it will not be required to be turned in. The only classes this does NOT apply too, are our Dual Credit classes at the HS. ECC is requiring all work/quizzes/tests to be completed and are assigning grades as normal. I hope this eases your mind a little. This situation is very unprecedented and we are going to be flexible. We will do our best to meet the needs of our kids and help them be successful. If you need anything or have other questions, please do not hesitate to contact us. We hope you and your kids are staying healthy!!

If you need anything or have other questions, please do not hesitate to contact us. We hope you and your kids are staying healthy!!

Attention Class of 2020!!

Jostens has contacted us and has a plan for getting the seniors their caps and gowns as well as any other items you have ordered. Jostens will be in Cuba on Tuesday, April 7th from 12-1 PM. In order to stay in line with the rules of social distancing, the Jostens representative will be located under the Middle School Awning. You will just drive to the location give him your name and he will get you your order.

They have asked that you please arrive at the time designated below:
12-12:15.. LAST NAME: A-F
12:15-12:30. LAST NAME: G-L
12:30-12:45. LAST NAME: M-R
12:45-1:00LAST NAME: S-Z

Please note, Cuba High Schools only role with Jostens is to allow them to sell the senior items so we are just passing along information that was given to us. If you have any questions or cannot make it at this time, please contact Sam Glennon at sam.glennon@jostens.com and he should be able to answer any of your questions.

Cuba Middle School
April 2 at 4:58 PM 路

Here's a story of a group of teachers who worked to-geth-er in 8th grade, and it was lit. But then a virus attacked the country and now at home, we sit.

Til this one day when we opened up the Zoom app and we knew that it was much more than a hunch we could meet each week on Thursdays and remain the 8th grade bunch.

The 8th-grade bunch, the 8th-grade bunch, we can now remain the 8th-grade bunch.

Check your Canvas, make good choices, and know that we love you and miss you!

post_text:
Seniors please review the following information regarding A+ Eligibility.

The Department of Higher Education has released the following updates to the A+ Program requirements for 2020 graduates.

*The Algebra I EOC requirement is waived for all 2020 high school seniors, including those who have already taken the exam but did not meet the requirement as well as those who have not yet taken the exam. Waiver of this requirement also exempts the 2020 seniors from having to meet the ACT math subscore/high school GPA alternative.

*The number of tutoring/mentoring hours have been reduced to 25 hours to accommodate those students who are unable to complete 50 hours prior to high school graduation.

Mrs. Hulbert has sent an email to all 2020 Seniors and parents/guardians who are currently pursuing A+ eligibility. If you didn't receive an email, please contact Mrs. Hulbert at thulbert@ccr2.org .

If interested, you can reference the memos on the A+ updates via the Missouri Department of Higher Educations website at https://dhewd.mo.gov/ppc/grants/aplusscholarship.php .

shared_text:
Cuba Lakes Golf Club
March 17 at 3:16 PM 路

We care about our community. Thats who we are and it has been since the beginning. We are completely vested in our community and the people around us. We will be offering sack lunches for the kids in our community while they are out of school with no strings attached. The lunches will be offered Monday through Friday from 11-2. The child must be present but no other purchases are necessary. The child can choose from PB&J or a grilled cheese sandwich. They will also receive an apple and a bag of chips. No advance notice of pick up is required. We hope to help support the kids of the community through this time off school. We also spurge show of support today for lunch and we will continue our food services in the days ahead. # Cuba Visitor

Cuba Elementary
March 2 at 6:38 PM 路

Cuba Elementary had some very special guests today! Soldiers in the U.S. Army stationed at Ft. Leonard Wood surprised our kids for Read Across America! All students were able to meet and be read to by a soldier. Thanks so much to these men and women for their service to our country, as well as taking time out of their days to make fantastic memories for our students!

post_text: RTI/RTC applications for the 2020-2021 school year have been handed out to all Sophomores who expressed interest and second year RTI/RTC students. Applications are due to the Counselors office no later than March 4, 2020 and reviewed based on the order they are returned. If you didnt receive an application or have questions, please contact Dr. Espinoza or Mrs. Hulbert.
